              Gee, James C},
  abstract = {A variant of the popular nonparametric nonuniform intensity
              normalization (N3) algorithm is proposed for bias field
              correction. Given the superb performance of N3 and its public
              availability, it has been the subject of several evaluation
              studies. These studies have demonstrated the importance of
              certain parameters associated with the B-spline least-squares
              fitting. We propose the substitution of a recently developed fast
              and robust B-spline approximation routine and a modified
              hierarchical optimization scheme for improved bias field
              correction over the original N3 algorithm. Similar to the N3
              algorithm, we also make the source code, testing, and technical
              documentation of our contribution, which we denote as ``N4ITK,''
              available to the public through the Insight Toolkit of the
